				\begin{document}$$\frac{\mathrm{VR}\ \mathrm{age}\ \mathrm{equivalent}}{\mathrm{chronological}\ \mathrm{age}}\times 100$$\end{document}VRageequivalentchronologicalage×100. Visual reception developmental quotients were used in all statistical models to control for the effect of cognitive development on motor skill acquisition.
